property_value: IAO:0000112 "Patient mentioned genetic risk for DVT/PE from commercial DNA testing kit of unknown type" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000057
name: clinical association
def: "A reified assertion relating two or more clinical entities, representing a contextualized clinical statement that can carry qualifiers such as negation, uncertainty, and temporality." []
is_a: IAO:0000030 ! information content entity
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Although these structures represent relationships between clinical entities, we model them as reified associations rather than relations, because they represent contextualized assertions with additional attributes (e.g., negation, uncertainty, temporality), which cannot be expressed using binary object properties in OWL.\nThese relations include the most frequently documented relation types as defined in:\nColicchio, Tiago K., Pavithra I. Dissanayake, and James J. Cimino. \"Formal representation of patients’ care context data: the path to improving the electronic health record.\" Journal of the American Medical Informatics Association 27, no. 11 (2020): 1648-1657." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000232 "CLCO represents temporal information through four orthogonal mechanisms: (1) temporal_frame (qualifier axis) -- document-relative context via has_temporal_frame, values historical/current/future/hypothetical; (2) completion_status (qualifier axis) -- workflow state via has_completion_status, values pending/in_progress/completed; (3) datatype time properties (data axis) -- computable timestamps via has_start_time, has_end_time, has_duration_value with xsd typed literals; (4) reified temporal associations (entity axis) -- narrative temporal entities such as has_onset, has_date, has_duration where the temporal expression is a first-class clinical_entity linked via has_object. These mechanisms are independent: a single association may carry values from any combination." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000058
name: has setting
def: "Inference about the location or setting where a clinical event happened." []
xref: OMOP_CONCEPT_ID:32462
is_a: CLCO:0000003 ! clinical administration
intersection_of: CLCO:0000057 ! clinical association
intersection_of: CLCO:0002501 CLCO:0000107 ! has object setting
relationship: CLCO:0002501 CLCO:0000107 ! has object setting
property_value: IAO:0000112 "He was given Zofran and meclizine at Urgent Care." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000060
name: intention
def: "Modifies a relation to indicate that the relation is intended rather than actual. Boolean." []
is_a: CLCO:0000068 ! statement qualifier
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Epistemic modality axis: captures whether the association describes an actual event or an intended/planned one. Orthogonal to temporal_frame (CLCO_0000082), which captures WHEN relative to the document, and completion_status (CLCO_0000063), which captures workflow state. An intended event may be past (we intended chemo but did not start), present, or future." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000062
name: recommended
def: "The modified relationship is recommended, for example an intervention, admission or some action. Boolean." []
is_a: CLCO:0000068 ! statement qualifier

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000063
name: completion status
def: "The workflow completion state of a process. Orthogonal to temporal_frame (which captures when relative to the document) and intention (which captures intent). A process may be pending regardless of whether its temporal frame is past, present, or future." []
xref: OMOP_CONCEPT_ID:4138595
xref: SNOMED:40642538
is_a: CLCO:0000068 ! statement qualifier
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Refactored from the original \"status\" class. Children include pending (moved from temporal), in_progress, and completed. Aligns with SNOMED procedure status qualifier values and EHR order status fields. No equivalent in NLP temporal annotation schemes like THYME or I2b2." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000065
name: pending
def: "The process described by the association has been initiated (e.g., ordered, requested) but has not yet reached its terminal output state. This is a workflow status, not a temporal frame: a pending result may refer to a process that occurred in the past (e.g., labs drawn yesterday, results pending)." []
xref: SNOMED:385645004
is_a: CLCO:0000063 ! completion status
disjoint_from: CLCO:0000087 ! in progress
property_value: IAO:0000112 "CT results pending" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Moved from subClassOf temporal (CLCO_0000064) to subClassOf completion_status (CLCO_0000063). The previous definition conflated workflow state with temporal frame and epistemic modality. See temporal_plan.txt Section 1A for rationale." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000067
name: association qualifier
def: "A modifier that provides additional context to a clinical association, such as temporal frame, certainty, negation, or participant-level detail." []
is_a: IAO:0000030 ! information content entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000068
name: statement qualifier
def: "An association qualifier that modifies the entire clinical statement, such as intention, recommendation or completion status." []
is_a: CLCO:0000067 ! association qualifier
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Qualifiers for the entire statement." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000069
name: predicate qualifier
def: "An association qualifier that modifies only the predicate (relationship type) of a clinical association, rather than the entire statement." []
is_a: CLCO:0000067 ! association qualifier
property_value: IAO:0000232 "For situations where the modifier of the predicate is different from the overall statement, these are likely to be rare." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000071
name: has aspect
def: "A finding association specifying which facet, part, or functional dimension of an entity is being referred to in the assertion." []
is_a: CLCO:0000057 ! clinical association
relationship: CLCO:0002501 CLCO:0000106 ! has object value
relationship: CLCO:0002502 CLCO:0000101 ! has subject finding
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Bone density is decreasing; cancer progression is rapid." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Aspect refers to which facet, part, or functional dimension of an entity is being referred to in the assertion. For example density or progression in bone density or cancer progression." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000072
name: has spatial orientation
def: "A finding association specifying the spatial orientation or anatomical direction of a finding relative to a body site." []
is_a: CLCO:0000057 ! clinical association
relationship: CLCO:0002501 CLCO:0000112 ! has object finding site
relationship: CLCO:0002502 CLCO:0000101 ! has subject finding
property_value: IAO:0000112 "The lesion is located on the anterior aspect of the left knee." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Spatial orientation qualifiers reuse PATO quality terms directly; CLCO defines only the attachment role." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000073
name: has laterality
def: "A finding association specifying the laterality (left, right, bilateral, unilateral, or midline) of a finding relative to a body site." []
is_a: CLCO:0000057 ! clinical association
relationship: CLCO:0002501 CLCO:0000112 ! has object finding site
relationship: CLCO:0002502 CLCO:0000101 ! has subject finding
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Right-sided pneumothorax; bilateral knee pain." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000232 "laterality_qualifier\n  ⊑ has_participant_qualifier only\n     (PATO:0000611  # left\n      or PATO:0000612  # right\n      or PATO:0000613  # bilateral\n      or PATO:0000614  # unilateral\n      or PATO:0000610) # midline" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000074
name: has severity
def: "A finding association specifying the severity or intensity of a finding or condition." []
xref: HP:0012824
is_a: CLCO:0000057 ! clinical association
relationship: CLCO:0002501 CLCO:0000106 ! has object value
relationship: CLCO:0002502 CLCO:0000101 ! has subject finding
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Severe abdominal pain; mild hearing loss." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000075
name: has descriptive value
def: "Information that qualitatively describes a finding, condition, or intervention." []
is_a: CLCO:0000024 ! has value
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Patient describes dizziness as a room spinning sensation." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000076
name: has quantifiable value
def: "Information that numerically quantifies a finding, condition, or intervention." []
xref: IAO:0000109
is_a: CLCO:0000024 ! has value
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Blood pressure 130/80 mmHg; hemoglobin 10.2 g/dL." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000077
name: suggests finding
def: "A finding or condition suggested by a diagnostic process, documentation, another finding or condition, or an intervention." []
is_a: CLCO:0000006 ! clinical explanation
relationship: CLCO:0002501 CLCO:0000101 ! has object finding
property_value: IAO:0000112 "The pink sputum suggests hemoptysis." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000080
name: negation
def: "Signifies that the qualified element is negated. Applies at any scope: statement-level negation negates the entire association; participant-level negation negates a specific subject or object." []
is_a: CLCO:0000067 ! association qualifier
property_value: IAO:0000112 "\"Patient denies chest pain\" (statement-level); \"Tenderness is present, but not in the right upper quadrant\" (participant-level)." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000081
name: uncertainty
def: "Signifies that the qualified element is uncertain or suspected. Applies at any scope: statement-level uncertainty qualifies the entire association; participant-level uncertainty qualifies a specific subject or object." []
is_a: CLCO:0000067 ! association qualifier

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000082
name: temporal frame
def: "The temporal location of the association relative to the moment of clinical documentation. Orthogonal to completion_status and intention." []
xref: biolink:temporal_context_qualifier
is_a: CLCO:0000067 ! association qualifier
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Replaces the deprecated temporal (CLCO_0000064). Aligns with THYME DocTimeRel and MedSpaCy temporal context flags. This axis answers WHEN relative to the document, not whether a process is complete (completion_status) or committed (intention)." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000083
name: historical
def: "The association describes an event or state that occurred before the time of the clinical document." []
xref: THYME:DocTimeRel_BEFORE
is_a: CLCO:0000082 ! temporal frame
disjoint_from: CLCO:0000084 ! current
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Patient underwent two kidney transplants (2002, 2012)" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000084
name: current
def: "The association describes an event or state that overlaps with the time of the clinical document." []
xref: THYME:DocTimeRel_OVERLAP
is_a: CLCO:0000082 ! temporal frame
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Currently on metformin" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000085
name: future
def: "The association describes an event or state that is expected to occur after the time of the clinical document." []
xref: THYME:DocTimeRel_AFTER
is_a: CLCO:0000082 ! temporal frame
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Chemotherapy will begin next Tuesday" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000086
name: hypothetical
def: "The association describes a conditional or contingent event that may or may not occur depending on specified circumstances." []
xref: THYME:contextual_modality_HYPOTHETICAL
is_a: CLCO:0000082 ! temporal frame
property_value: IAO:0000112 "If fever persists, start vancomycin" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Sits at the boundary of temporal frame and modality. Placed under temporal_frame because NLP systems (THYME contextual_modality, MedSpaCy is_hypothetical) treat it as a document-context label at the same annotation layer as historical/current/future." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000087
name: in progress
def: "The process described by the association is actively executing but has not yet reached its terminal state." []
is_a: CLCO:0000063 ! completion status
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Antibiotics course ongoing" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000088
name: completed
def: "The process described by the association has reached its terminal output state." []
is_a: CLCO:0000063 ! completion status
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Physical therapy completed" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000100
name: clinical entity
def: "A core clinical entity over which all clinical context associations occur." []
is_a: BFO:0000001 ! entity
property_value: IAO:0000232 "The 14 core clinical entity classes defined in:\nColicchio, Tiago K., Pavithra I. Dissanayake, and James J. Cimino. \"Formal representation of patients’ care context data: the path to improving the electronic health record.\" Journal of the American Medical Informatics Association 27, no. 11 (2020): 1648-1657.\nAll of these should correspond to a subject or object in relations extracted by NLP systems. The exception to that is patient which may be inferred." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000101
name: finding
def: "A clinical finding of any type, including conditions." []
xref: biolink:DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Was finding/condition in original paper, can treat condition as a subclass if needed." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000102
name: intervention
def: "An intervention to treat or diagnose a finding/condition or the patient" []
xref: biolink:Procedure
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000103
name: time
def: "Numerical or narrative temporal data elements" []
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Moved from subClassOf task (CLCO_0000109) to subClassOf clinical_entity (CLCO_0000100). Time is a first-class clinical entity type, not a subtype of task." xsd:string

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000104
name: reason
def: "Justifications and reasons for ordering, performing, planning, or discontinuing an intervention or diagnostic process" []
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000105
name: course
def: "Course of a finding/condition" []
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000106
name: value
def: "Any numerical or narrative description of a finding/condition or intervention" []
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000107
name: setting
def: "Health care setting or location" []
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000108
name: clinician
def: "Health care professional, unlike SNOMED, includes only people working directly with patients such as physicians, nurses, etc... Adminstrative healthcare professionals such as healthcare billing coders are not included." []
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000109
name: task
def: "Any healthcare related task not related to direct clinical activities (e.g., phone call or uploading a medical record file)." []
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000110
name: patient
def: "The patient entity" []
xref: biolink:Case
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000111
name: documentation
def: "Clinical documentation, e.g., progress notes, imaging reports" []
xref: IAO:0000310
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000112
name: finding site
def: "Anatomical site of a finding/condition" []
xref: SNOMED:123037004
xref: UBERON:0001062
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000113
name: patient state
def: "Patient state, e.g., stable, improving. The overall patient state, not whether a particular disease or condition is stable or improving." []
is_a: CLCO:0000100 ! clinical entity

[Term]
id: CLCO:0000114
name: is discharged
def: "Statement indicating that the patient has been discharged from a clinical setting" []
xref: OMOP_CONCEPT_ID:4137031
xref: SNOMED:58000006
is_a: CLCO:0000058 ! has setting
relationship: CLCO:0002502 CLCO:0000110 ! has subject patient
property_value: IAO:0000112 "Patient discharged this morning with family" xsd:string

[Term]
id: IAO:0000030
name: information content entity
def: "A generically dependent continuant that is about some entity." []

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002000
name: has association qualifier
def: "A modifier of a clinical association" []
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Analogous to RO:0000053 (has characteristic) in that the association bears the qualifier, but not declared as a sub-property because BFO type constraints require the bearer to be an independent continuant and the characteristic to be a specifically dependent continuant. CLCO associations are information content entities and qualifiers are not modeled as BFO dependent continuants." xsd:string
property_value: seeAlso RO:0000053
domain: CLCO:0000057 ! clinical association
range: CLCO:0000067 ! association qualifier

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002002
name: has intention
def: "Relates a clinical association to its intention qualifier, indicating that the association is intended rather than actual." []
range: CLCO:0000060 ! intention
is_a: CLCO:0003000 ! has statement qualifier

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002003
name: has recommended
def: "Relates a clinical association to its recommendation qualifier, indicating that the association represents a clinical recommendation." []
range: CLCO:0000062 ! recommended
is_a: CLCO:0003000 ! has statement qualifier

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002004
name: has negation status
def: "Relates a clinical association to its negation status, indicating whether the asserted relationship is negated." []
range: CLCO:0000080 ! negation
is_a: CLCO:0002000 ! has association qualifier

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002009
name: has uncertainty status
def: "Relates a clinical association to its uncertainty qualifier, indicating that the asserted relationship is uncertain or suspected." []
range: CLCO:0000081 ! uncertainty
is_a: CLCO:0002000 ! has association qualifier

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002100
name: has participant qualifier
def: "Relates a clinical association to a qualifier that modifies a participant (subject or object) rather than the overall statement or predicate." []
is_a: CLCO:0002000 ! has association qualifier

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002500
name: has association participant
def: "Relates a clinical association to a clinical entity that participates in it as either the subject or the object." []
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Analogous to RO:0000057 (has participant) but not declared as a sub-property because RO:0000057 relates a process (occurrent) to a continuant, whereas CLCO clinical associations are reified information content entities (subClassOf IAO:0000030), not processes. CLCO uses a statement reification pattern (n-ary relation) in which subject and object slots connect an association class to the entities it asserts a relationship between. This pattern has no direct equivalent in RO, which models relations as direct object properties between BFO-typed instances." xsd:string
property_value: seeAlso RO:0000057

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002501
name: has object
def: "Relates a clinical association (an asserted statement) to the entity that occupies the object position in that association." []
property_value: IAO:0000232 "No direct RO equivalent exists. This property fills the object slot in a reified clinical statement (n-ary relation pattern). RO models relations as direct object properties, not as reified statements with named participant slots. See parent property CLCO:0002500 for further rationale." xsd:string
is_a: CLCO:0002500 ! has association participant

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002502
name: has subject
def: "Relates a clinical association (an asserted statement) to the entity that occupies the subject position in that association." []
property_value: IAO:0000232 "No direct RO equivalent exists. This property fills the subject slot in a reified clinical statement (n-ary relation pattern). RO models relations as direct object properties, not as reified statements with named participant slots. See parent property CLCO:0002500 for further rationale." xsd:string
is_a: CLCO:0002500 ! has association participant

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002603
name: has temporal frame
def: "Relates a clinical association to its temporal frame value (historical, current, future, or hypothetical) indicating when the association holds relative to the clinical document." []
xref: biolink:temporal_context_qualifier
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Not a sub-property of RO:0002222 (temporally related to) because RO temporal relations use Allen interval algebra to order two occurrents (processes) relative to each other, whereas CLCO temporal frame is a categorical document-relative qualifier (historical/current/future/hypothetical) attached to a reified information entity. The RO_0001900 (temporal interpretation) annotation is retained to indicate that this property has temporal semantics." xsd:string
property_value: RO:0001900 RO:0001901
property_value: seeAlso RO:0002222
range: CLCO:0000082 ! temporal frame
is_a: CLCO:0002000 ! has association qualifier

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0002604
name: has completion status
def: "Relates a clinical association to its workflow completion status (pending, in_progress, or completed). Orthogonal to temporal frame and intention." []
property_value: IAO:0000232 "Not a sub-property of has_temporal_context because completion status is not a temporal concept. A pending process may be temporally past (labs drawn yesterday, results pending)." xsd:string
property_value: RO:0001900 RO:0001901
range: CLCO:0000063 ! completion status
is_a: CLCO:0003000 ! has statement qualifier

[Typedef]
id: CLCO:0003000
name: has statement qualifier
def: "Relates a clinical association to a statement-level qualifier that modifies the entire assertion, such as intention, recommendation, or completion status." []
is_a: CLCO:0002000 ! has association qualifier

